[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_json_get` function.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability type: stack-based buffer overflow in the JSON parsing logic of the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMongoose codebase.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Important observations:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Fuzzing engine: libFuzzer, mode: interactive.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Fuzzer invocation: `[0m[35m/out/[0m[95mfuzz[0m[39m -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The overflow is reported at `json.[0m[1;92mc:186:28[0m[39m`, with the offending stack frame [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstarting at `json.[0m[1;92mc:127[0m[39m`.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The `nesting` array spans offsets [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in the stack frame, and the faulty [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrite occurs at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m, just past the end.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The sanitizer shadow bytes confirm the write lands in the stack left redzone, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating an out-of-bounds access.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- To get a holistic view of the issue, the following parts of the codebase should [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe examined:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The implementation of `mg_json_get` in `src/mongoose/src/json.c`, focusing on [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer allocations and index calculations for the `nesting` array.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The fuzz test harness in `src/mongoose/test/fuzz.c`, specifically how inputs [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare prepared and passed to `mg_json_get`.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Related JSON parsing functions or helpers in `src/mongoose/src/json.c` that [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmanipulate the same or adjacent buffers.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Any boundary checks around array accesses in the JSON module that could prevent[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor trigger this overflow.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m---[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m183[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m pos++;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m184[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m185[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m186[0m[39m:          break;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.h:[0m[1;36m6[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m12[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m:#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m:#define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH [0m[1;36m30[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m8[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m9[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m10[0m[39m:#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m11[0m[39m:#define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m60[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m12[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:167[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m176[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m167[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m168[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'.'[0m[39m && ci == ei[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m169[0m[39m:            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m If we start the object, reset array indices[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m170[0m[39m:            ed++, pos++, ci = ei = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m171[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m172[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m173[0m[39m:          expecting = S_KEY;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m174[0m[39m:          break;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m175[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m176[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:175[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m186[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m175[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m176[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m177[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m && ei == ci[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m178[0m[39m:            ed++, pos++, ci = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m179[0m[39m:            for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mei = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[32m'[0m[32m][0m[32m'[0m[39m && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[32m'\0'[0m[39m; pos++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m180[0m[39m:              ei *= [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m181[0m[39m:              ei += path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m - [0m[32m'0'[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m182[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m183[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m pos++;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m184[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m185[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m186[0m[39m:          break;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stack buffer `nesting` is declared with size MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe code allows `depth` to grow up to MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The checks `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` are insufficient to prevent [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrites beyond the [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m‐byte `nesting` array, leading to a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m‐byte overflow when [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`depth` is between [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m.  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. High‐Level Fix  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Option A [0m[1;39m([0m[39mPreferred[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Increase the `nesting` buffer size to match the maximum [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpermitted nesting level so that no overflow can occur.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Change the declaration of `nesting` from `unsigned char [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;` to `unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;`.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This aligns the physical buffer capacity with the logical limit checked by the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode.  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Option B: Tighten the depth‐check logic to enforce the smaller buffer limit.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replace both `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` checks with `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` so that the code errors out before exceeding the [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m‐byte [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This reduces the allowable nesting to [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m, preventing the overflow without [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincreasing stack usage.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed Patch Steps [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOption A[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Open `src/json.c` around line [0m[1;36m130[0m[39m.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Locate the declaration:  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Change it to:  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. Add a `#if`‐`#error` guard just after the includes to catch future [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmismatches:  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        #if MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING < MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        #  error [0m[32m"MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING must be >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH"[0m[39m  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        #endif  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   e. Rebuild and rerun the fuzz target; the AddressSanitizer error should [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdisappear.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Logic  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing depth checks [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remain untouched, preserving the original maximum‐nesting [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbehavior.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No changes to the fuzz harness or JSON parsing logic beyond buffer sizing, so [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting tests and fuzzer harness continue to operate identically, only without [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggering an overflow.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Justification  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Aligning the physical buffer size with the logical limit is a minimal‐impact [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchange that directly addresses the overflow root cause.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It avoids altering the intended JSON‐depth behavior or adding overly [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrestrictive checks.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Adding a compile‐time guard prevents future macro misconfiguration.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects & Mitigations  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stack frame of `mg_json_get` grows by [0m[1;39m([0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING - [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m30[0m[39m additional bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. This is negligible in typical [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39menvironments.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If very deep JSON structures [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > [0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m were previously valid in production [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode, this change preserves that behavior as long as depth ≤ MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The compile‐time guard ensures that if someone later changes one macro without[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe other, a build‐error will highlight the mismatch.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. References  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The bug is analogous to previous fixes in this module where physical buffer [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marrays were aligned to logical depth limits [0m[1;39m([0m[39msee e.g. `mg_http.c` handling of [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheader stack frames[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No changes to public APIs or harness; existing JSON path semantics remain [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconsistent.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:175[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m186[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m175[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m180[0m[39m:              ei *= [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m181[0m[39m:              ei += path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m - [0m[32m'0'[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m182[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m183[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m pos++;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m184[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m185[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m186[0m[39m:          break;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Align Buffer Size and Nesting Limit:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `src/json.c`, change the declaration of the local stack buffer `nesting` to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muse the same macro as the nesting‐limit guard:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Before:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m After:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This ensures the buffer is large enough to hold as many depth levels as the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode allows.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Correct the Off‐by‐One in the Nesting‐Depth Guard:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In both the object‐start [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and array‐start [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m branches, change the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguard condition from `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Before:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m After:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By using `>=`, any attempt to index `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` when `depth == [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` is prevented, eliminating the one‐byte overflow.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Deprecate MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH [0m[1;39m([0m[39moptional cleanup[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Since `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` is no longer used in `json.c`, consider removing or [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maliasing it in `src/json.h` to avoid confusion:[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m In src/json.h, after MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING is defined:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #undef MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH  MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This maintains backward compatibility for any code that references [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` elsewhere.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preserve Critical Logic:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing logic that updates `depth`, pushes/pops from `nesting`, and [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnavigates the `path` should remain untouched except for the guard and buffer size. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No fuzz‐harness, test code, or other JSON‐parsing logic is altered. The only [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchange is to synchronize buffer size with its guard.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Side‐Effect Analysis:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stack usage for `nesting` increases [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfrom [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m to [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m bytes by default[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtrivial.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stricter guard [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`>=`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m prevents one more level of nesting than before, but [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis matches the intended maximum [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing functionality and tests are preserved; only pathological over‐deep [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJSON inputs will now return `MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP` earlier, preventing crashes.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Justification:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The AddressSanitizer reports clearly pin an out‐of‐bounds write at [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` when the buffer was only [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes or even [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m bytes with an [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moff‐by‐one.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By unifying the buffer size and the guard macro, and fixing the comparison to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`>=`, we guarantee `depth` is always strictly less than the buffer length before [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindexing.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This approach mirrors standard patterns elsewhere in the codebase [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlimiting path‐length buffers early[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and minimizes changes to maintain readability [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand correctness.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. No Other Code Affected:[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No changes are made to the fuzz target, test harness, or any external [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdependencies.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No broad exception‐catching or test removal is needed.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch is confined to `json.c` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand optionally a small header alias in [0m     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is a stack-buffer-overflow in the function `mg_json_get` [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39msrc/json.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when running the libFuzzer harness. AddressSanitizer reports a [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mone‐byte write past the end of the local array `nesting`. A patch was applied to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchange the array size from `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` to `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` and to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtighten the boundary checks [0m[1;39m([0m[39mchanging `depth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` to `depth >= [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. After applying the patch, the same overflow is still [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggered at the same location and offset, indicating that the changes did not [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meliminate the out‐of‐bounds access.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A fuzzing session with AddressSanitizer enabled crashes inside `mg_json_get` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m in src/json.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The error log shows:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • A write of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m beyond a stack‐allocated buffer  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • The overflow occurs at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m of the `nesting` array, whose bounds are [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `nesting` is declared as `unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;`  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stack frame details:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Depth counter increments lead to an index ≥ [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • No adequate check prevents writing to `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` when `depth` reaches [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe array’s capacity  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Observations in the Initial Log  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash always traces back to `mg_json_get` at the same source line.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in test/fuzz.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m simply feeds [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marbitrary JSON data to `mg_json_get`.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The issue is isolated to stack memory in the JSON parsing routine, not in the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mharness code.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The declaration of `nesting` was changed:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```diff[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     + unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Boundary checks on entering `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` were updated:[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```diff[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     + if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The intention was to align the buffer size with the macro used for maximum [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnesting and to disallow depth values equal to the buffer length.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Post-Patch Log  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After rebuild, the same AddressSanitizer report appears:[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • One‐byte write at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m in `nesting`  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Overflow annotation still points to line [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The buffer bounds remained unchanged in practice or the new macro value did [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot enlarge the array sufficiently.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash signature and stack trace are virtually identical to the pre‐patch [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrun.[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Definitions of `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` and `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` macros and their [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnumeric values.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The logic in `mg_json_get` that increments `depth` and indexes [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All code paths that touch `nesting`, including array entry [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and object [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m handling.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overall algorithm for tracking key/array nesting to ensure that every [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincrement of `depth` is guarded.  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether any off‐by‐one or misalignment between macros has left the buffer too [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msmall relative to worst‐case JSON inputs.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m215[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m + n >= len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_NOT_FOUND;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m216[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth < ed[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_NOT_FOUND;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m217[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos - [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[32m'.'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_NOT_FOUND;[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m218[0m[39m:          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;35mprintf[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"K %s [0m[32m[[0m[32m%.*s[0m[32m][0m[32m [0m[32m[[0m[32m%.*s[0m[32m][0m[32m %d %d %d %d %d\n"[0m[39m, path, pos, path, n,[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m219[0m[39m:          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m        &s[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, n, depth, ed, ci, ei[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m220[0m[39m:          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m  [0m[1;35mNOTE[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcpq[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: in the check sequence below is important.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.h:[0m[1;36m6[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m12[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m:#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m:#define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH [0m[1;36m30[0m                                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m10[0m[39m:#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m11[0m[39m:#define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m60[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m12[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:166[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m168[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m166[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m167[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m168[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'.'[0m[39m && ci == ei[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:175[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m177[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m175[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m176[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m177[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m && ei == ci[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Unify depth-related macros**  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Currently, two different macros control related limits:  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault [0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ⇒ size of local buffer `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault [0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ⇒ limit used in boundary checks  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This mismatch allows `depth` to grow up to [0m[1;36m59[0m[39m, and then write `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m59[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mand even `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m into a [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m-byte array, causing a one‐byte overflow at [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Modify `src/json.h`**  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Change the definition of `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` to alias `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mso there is a single authoritative limit:  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```diff[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m #ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m-#define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH [0m[1;36m30[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m+#define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH [0m[1;36m30[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m #endif[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m9[0m[39m:[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m-#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m11[0m[39m-#define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m60[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m-#endif[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m+#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m11[0m[39m+#define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m+#endif[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This ensures that both `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` and `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` have the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame numeric value [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m30[0m[39m by default, or any user‐provided override[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and eliminates [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe two‐macro confusion.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Adjust boundary checks in `src/json.c`**  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All checks protecting against over‐nesting should use `>=` rather than `>` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mi.e., disallow `depth == MAX`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and refer to the unified macro. Specifically, in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe ‘[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m’ and ‘[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m’ handlers:  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```diff[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     --- a/src/json.c[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +++ b/src/json.c[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     @@ [0m[1;36m-165[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m +[0m[1;36m165[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m @@[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           …[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           …[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     @@ [0m[1;36m-174[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m +[0m[1;36m174[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m @@[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           …[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           …[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - These changes guarantee that any attempt to push beyond the allowed maximum [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnesting is caught before writing to `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Declare `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` with the unified macro**  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `src/json.c`, change the array declaration to use the unified [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich now equals `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m so the code remains [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclear that the array size matches its usage:  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```diff[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     --- a/src/json.c[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +++ b/src/json.c[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     @@ [0m[1;36m-130[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m +[0m[1;36m130[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m @@[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       enum [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m S_VALUE, S_KEY, S_COLON, S_COMMA_OR_EOO [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m expecting = S_VALUE;[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     + unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       int i = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, j = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, depth = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, ed = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, pos = [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m, ci = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m, ei = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - With `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` aliased to `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`, the array has a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlength that matches the tightest limit.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Reapply existing patches**  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure that the `>=` boundary‐check changes from the previous patch attempt [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare included.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm that no other code paths modify `depth` without guard checks [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m`,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` increments are now safe[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Justification and side-effect analysis**  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This strategy resolves the out‐of‐bounds write by eliminating the two‐macro [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmismatch and tightening the overflow guards.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing logic for parsing and tracking nesting is preserved; only the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnumeric limits and checks change.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Tests and external consumers that may redefine `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` will [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mautomatically have `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` adjusted to match, preventing a [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregression.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No harness code or utility functions are modified; fuzzing behavior and test [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msuites remain valid.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. **Verification steps**  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rebuild with AddressSanitizer and rerun libFuzzer; ensure no [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack-buffer-overflow in `mg_json_get`.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Optionally, add a regression‐test JSON that tries nesting deeper than the new [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlimit and verify it returns `MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP` without crashing.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run existing JSON‐unit tests to confirm no functionality break.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is an AddressSanitizer–detected stack-buffer-overflow in the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction `mg_json_get` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `src/json.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when a fuzzer exercises deeply nested JSON[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths. The overflow occurs in the local array `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, which holds per-depth [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath indices. A patch attempt was made to replace the hard-coded [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` value with `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`, adjust the array declaration [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto use the updated macro, and tighten the depth-check conditions from `>` to `>=`. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the same overflow error recurs at the same offset, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating the patch did not eliminate the out-of-bounds write.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
