[2;36m                    [0m         [39min `json.c`.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer reports a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte write overflow on the stack at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minside the `nesting` array.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stack trace highlights the overflow in `mg_json_get` at line [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m of `json.c`, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggered by `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = …`.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `nesting` array is defined as having length `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreviously `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but the code allows `depth` to reach at least [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat same value before bounds checking triggers.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Observations from the Initial Log  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The buffer overflow is reproducible with a single fuzzer input.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The exact overflow offset is [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m, implying the array was allocated for [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m or a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msimilarly small number of entries, yet the code writes at index [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The failure always occurs in `mg_json_get`, not in the harness or any external[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibrary.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `src/json.h`, the macro  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `#define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m`  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     was changed to  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `#define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     assuming `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` is defined elsewhere to represent a desired [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaximum nesting depth.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `src/json.c` near line [0m[1;36m127[0m[39m, the local declaration  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;`  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     was changed to  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;`  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In the sections handling `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` tokens, the checks  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;`  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     were tightened to  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;`  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - These edits aim to unify the depth limit macros and prevent writes when [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`depth` equals the limit.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Post-Patch Log  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The same sanitizer error appears at the same code location [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m186[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow offset remains [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m, writing one byte beyond the allocated range of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting`.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The log otherwise parallels the initial run, confirming the patch did not [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malter the out-of-bounds behavior.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The definition and value of `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor any alias[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in `json.h`—why[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis it not preventing the overflow?  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The full implementation of `mg_json_get` around the array access: how `depth` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis incremented and how/when bounds checks occur relative to writes into `nesting`. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any other code paths that modify `depth` or write into `nesting` without [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecking against the macro.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Possible inconsistencies between compile-time macro values and assumptions in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe code.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is an AddressSanitizer-detected stack-buffer-overflow in the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction `mg_json_get` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `src/json.[0m[1;92mc:186[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, where the local array `nesting` is [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflowed by one byte. The patch attempt increased the maximum allowed depth [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstants [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` and `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and adjusted boundary [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks from `>` to `>=` against `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`. After applying these [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchanges, the fuzzer still reproduces the same one‐byte write overflow at the same [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode location, indicating the patch did not prevent the buffer overflow.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A fuzzer run triggers AddressSanitizer to report a stack-buffer-overflow in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_json_get`.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow occurs on a one-byte write [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`WRITE of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `nesting` array.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The array `nesting` is declared as `unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` defaulting to [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m, but ASan indicates the overflow happens [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m, well beyond that size.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The backtrace shows the error originates at line [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m of `json.c`, during JSON [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing, as exercised by `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Important Observations  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stack frame for `mg_json_get` contains one object, `nesting`, spanning [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow write targets `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, exactly one byte past its upper [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbound.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The code uses two related constants: `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuffer size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting limit[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. By default, `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` is [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` is [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `json.h`, `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` was increased from [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m to [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` was redefined to equal `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` instead of a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mseparate value.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `json.c`, the local declaration was changed from `unsigned char [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` to use `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Boundary checks for object [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and array [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m entries were tightened [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfrom  [0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     to  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Result After Patch  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer run post-patch still triggers an AddressSanitizer [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack-buffer-overflow at the same code location [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`src/json.[0m[1;92mc:186[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow again occurs at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m in the `nesting` array, suggesting the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marray is still allocated with a length of [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor effectively smaller than the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindex being written[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No change in crash signature indicates the patch did not alter the underlying [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrite behavior or correctly resize the buffer.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The declarations and uses of `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` and `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboth header [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`json.h`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and source [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`json.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to verify they are consistently [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapplied.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The code paths in `mg_json_get` that modify `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, especially [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maround line [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m, to understand how `depth` can exceed the actual buffer size.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any other code that manipulates `depth` or `nesting` indirectly [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincremental updates, path parsing logic[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to ensure depth never grows beyond the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintended limit.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
